The South African government is determined to achieved improved credit ratings, the Treasury said on Friday after S&P Global Ratings affirmed the sovereign’s debt at sub-investment grade ‘BB’/’BB+’. “Taking steps to improve business confidence even further, achieving higher economic growth, fast-tracking the (state-owned firms’) reform agenda, and ultimately restoring the country’s investment grade credit rating, remains a top priority,” the Treasury said in a statement. Read S&P affirms SA rating, keeps stable outlook